1�To feel it with my own whiskerrrs, and find out...
1�No, I'm not. I couldn't face them alone.
1�I should...have brrrought you with...me. I realize that now.
1�(No, I'm not rrready to go! I have to tell them what I saw...)
1�(I don't care. As long as I can prrrotect everyone, I don't care what happens to me!)
1�I hearrrd a voice calling out to me. I can't explain it...
1�But whatever it was trrransported me back here, to this world.
1�Lhe...the dangers of Eastern Ulbuka are graverrrr than you could possibly imagine.
1�Neither you nor anyone else must ever trrread upon its forbidden grounds!
1�Those fairy tales we hearrrd as children...true, all of them...down to the last word.
1�Lhe, give me your worrrd...that you'll never go any further into the woods.
1�B-but you saw what she had become!
1�Leathery Lhe! We gotta get outta here, n-now!
1�Wow! Adventurers from the Middle Lands are unlike anything I've ever seen!
1�Do you think we should stop the colonization effort? The fairy tales she mentioned...she must have meant the will of the founder.
1�This!? You were worried about a funguarrr!?
1�What is this thing? I've never seen anything like it before!
1�What's wrong with me...? Somehow this feels so familiar...
1�Shla, but...how? How did it turrrn out like this?
1�Shhh. That's not imporrrtant. What matters is that you're here, back with me.
1�You two boobs think I'm going to stand down now?
1�Imbeciles! You didn't think a lost parrradise was waiting for us, did you!?
1�I don't care if we're grrreeted by the flames of hell themselves. We've got a task to do, and we're going to do it.
1�Hah. The wailing of your spirit cried out, and now--well, look at this.
1�This will make an excellent specimen. I know what you desire. And I may yet grant it to you.
1�But, yes, you are indeed dead. To remain in this world would require an immense amount of power. Even if you were to find a new vessel, you won't be completely whole.
1�Hahaha. Then let me try this codex I grabbed off a wandering Goblin. We'll see if you are still pleased with your choice.
1�Your passions and emotions may just let you survive this ritual. Enjoy your new ??leash?? on life.
1�How about it?Promise to go to Bastok.Not with that attitude!
1�(...Understood. Don't concern yourself with the latter--many other agents are already in place. Proceed with your current mission. We await further details.)
1�This outcropping is the perfect spot to begin!
1�(To think that this technopedia my damned father gave me when I was ten would actually prove of use...unfathomable.)
1�(Normal kids get toys or sweets for their birthdays. Not me...but here I am now, all because of this little book.)
1�Gah! For the love of...you gave me a good scare!
1�Who are you, and how do you know my name!?
1�Further, what're you doing all the way out here?
1�Hey now! What gives you the right to call me ??Junior??!? I hate when people call me that!
1�I've got a real name, you know. ??Midras.??
1�How did you even know that nickname, anyway?
1�Oh, now I get it. That cursed Tarutaru told you.
1�An adventurer from the Middle Lands. That must make you a pioneer.
1�You must have gotten here by the waypoints then. Pshaw.
1�Not all of us took the easy way, you know. When I first came here, I had to take a ship across the tumultuous Sea of Zafmlug. Now just about anyone can make the journey.
1�No seasickness, no lack of food, no worry about being capsized by some deep-sea denizen. You should count your blessings.
1�I suppose you didn't come here to be lectured.
1�However, while we're on the topic, those waypoints you use were developed right here in Adoulin, by the Inventors' Coalition.
1�The wonders they come up with day by day never cease to amaze me.
1�I know making the trip here was the right decision--difficult though it was--after seeing all they do. I've learned more here in a week than I could in Jeuno in years.
1�...Is that so? Amchuchu herself? She's always worried about how I'm holding up.
1�Sorry that you came all this way, but no matter how much I want to go back, I can't yet. Things are more...difficult than I anticipated.
1�Aha! That gives me an idea. Being an adventurer means you can use the waypoints, can't you?
1�Allow me to introduce myself properly: I'm Midras. Charmed, I'm sure.
1�Now then, if Amchuchu is waiting, then I can't really dillydally here any longer.
1� , I know we've just met, but I need you to do something for me. Go to Bastok and get a certain concoction from an inventor named Cid.
1�I shouldn't talk about him like some stranger, because he is my father, after all...
1�I'm sure you must know all about me by now. <Snort>
1�(I'd give my life savings to have her keep her trap shut.)
1�Anyway, I need that concoction from pops to prepare my own explosive compound.
1�I ran out, you see. It's my own fault for not properly checking my supplies.
1�What I need you to get is a bit on the rare side, and it would take days to find some here in Adoulin. But pops has some in his workshop. Of that I can be sure.
1�I know you'll help me out with this.
1�I knew I could count on you.
1�The compound names are a bit technical, so here...take this list so you don't have to remember it all. Give it to my old man, would you kindly?
1�I know you'll come around. After all, this is the first step in helping Adoulin feed its populace!
1�Well, well, look who the Mithra dragged in.
1�This is unbelievable. I told you, my name is MID-RAS.
1�Can't find any good help around here. I bet you didn't even bring back what I requested.
?.�Oh ho, you actually did it. Color me impressed. Now, to just do a little fiddling around...
1�What are you, scared? Get back over here.
1�Not all explosives are about making things burst into flames. Sometimes a more delicate approach is required. But I suppose I can't fault an amateur such as yourself for not knowing.
1�You see, even though this explosion was rather tame, it helped me excavate exactly what I need.
1�Accept it or be left in the dust!
1�But I'll leave the lessons for when you've become a bit more refined.
1�Damn, I forgot Amchuchu was waiting for me.
1� , there's one more task I have for you. Bring this back to the Inventors' Coalition for me.
1�I've got a bit more preparation to do here.
1�(This is Omega. I have successfully found employ at the Inventors' Coalition in Adoulin and am currently working to gather information about their unique technologies.)
1�(I am also in the process of collecting intel about the other coalitions, groups, and organizations in the nation. I will submit a full briefing once I have more to share.)
1�(However, I have run into difficulties finding reliable sources regarding these runic technologies and the underlying structure behind geomancy.)
1�(And isn't he also the technician dispatched from the Middle Lands?)
1�(??Omega??... this whole deal sounds very secretive. And Gratzigg doesn't like secrets.)
1�(I must return to headquarters and apprise him of the situation...)
1�Oh my Gob! You're one of those adventurerurers, aren't ya?You got nothin' on me, ?[man./lady.] I was just mindin' my own businesesess, lookin' for junk an' stuff.
1�Hey, watch out. You don't wanna fight me. I'll turn you into meat jerky!Wait, how about you and me be friends instead? Sound good?
1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
1�Would you like to hear a story?No, thank you.Let's hear one.
